On 7/11/05 8:37 AM, "Charles Durrrant" <charliedurrant(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

> I don't have any dash pots - should I invest some time in getting some?

You don't need them to drive the bus but they smooth out the engine by
slowing the throttle's return back to closed. I've also found they smooth
out the gear shifts by keeping the rpms up slightly.

There is only one on the left carb.

